cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CC

This paper deals with the problem of overfitting in machine learning, specifically in the context of multiclass classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information theory, as it uses Hamming queries to reconstruct sequences, so cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and computational efficiency, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with artificial intelligence and classification, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
